HEADWORD: Arson
<hw>Ar"son</hw> <pr>(⟦aum⟧r"s'n; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>arson</ets>, <ets>arsun</ets>, fr. L. <ets>ardere</ets>,
<ets>arsum</ets>, to burn.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The malicious
burning of a dwelling house or outhouse of another man, which by the
common law is felony; the malicious and voluntary firing of a building
or ship.</def> <rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

